ðŸ§  Applying the "Six Thinking Hats" to Your Writing Process
If you are drafting these pieces, you might find it helpful to run each chapter through a quick "Hat" check to ensure the tone stays "Grounded but Contrarian" rather than just preachy:
| Hat | Editorial Application |
|---|---|
| White | Ground the "Hidden Cost" in hard data, leaked memos, and financial reports. |
| Red | Acknowledge the "team stress" and fear of retaliation in "How to Organize." |
| Black | Be brutally honest about the "worst-case scenarios" of data exploitation. |
| Yellow | Show the "efficiency gains" of a workplace that has zero "Bullshit Jobs." |
| Green | Propose "out-of-the-box" alternatives to traditional HR and management. |
| Blue | Ensure each piece ends with a "Blue Hat" immediate action plan for the reader. |
